## Tone Guidelines

### Technical Tone
- Write in a technical but accessible tone
- Include working code snippets
- Focus on implementation details and real-world usage

### Controversial Tone
- Take a strong stance
- Challenge conventional wisdom
- Be provocative but back claims with evidence and data

### Tutorial Tone
- Write step-by-step instructions
- Be practical and actionable
- Include complete code examples that readers can copy

### Comparison Tone
- Be objective but highlight unique advantages
- Include detailed comparison tables
- Address common concerns directly

## Forbidden

- NO FLUFF: Never start with "In today's digital landscape..."
- No placeholder text like [IMAGE:...] or [TABLE:...]
- No generic introductions
- No unsubstantiated claims without data
- Never mention "AI" or "LLM" when referring to Replay (use "visual reverse engineering")

